He could barely say Mumma
and now he says
“Momma, my heart feels small when you’re not here,and big  again when you come back. Little did we know mine feels the same 

Watching you grow brings a quiet, lasting joy.
So kind, so sensitive 
so smart—just like Papa.
I hope you never stop chasing sunsets,
finding shells 🌈 
and spinning stories, my storyteller.♥️
Okay, bye now consider me unavailable.
We’re busy with big big cake 🍰 
and shadding some happy tears🥹
He's ten !🎈
